  "title": "Audit Assistant Manager",
  "description": "<p><strong>    SUMMARY</strong></p>\n<p>    You will be instrumental in overseeing and managing audit engagements, offering guidance to staff,</p>\n<p>    and ensuring adherence to professional standards while addressing risks. Understanding clients'</p>\n<p>    industries, performance drivers, and emerging trends will be pivotal in planning engagement</p>\n<p>    objectives effectively and maintaining compliance.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>     ESSENTIAL</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Sound knowledge of Singapore Financial Reporting Standards and Singapore Standards on Auditing.</li>\n  <li>Excellent interpersonal, written and verbal communication skills. The ability to read and interpret technical standards and routine commercial contracts is essential.</li>\n  <li>Possess a strong affinity for numbers and ability to interpret financial data.</li>\n  <li>Demonstrate an ability to lead and motivate others.</li>\n  <li>Have strong initiative and self-motivation.</li>\n  <li>Be able to work under pressure and meet deadlines.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>QUALIFICATION &amp; EXPERIENCE</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>ACCA or accounting degree qualification which is recognised by ISCA, <u>or</u> have the Chartered Accountant of Singapore qualification.</li>\n  <li>Have at least 4 years of relevant audit experience in a professional accounting firm in Singapore</li>\n  <li>Knowledge of Caseware software would be an added advantage</li>\n</ul>",
